<HEAD>News Editor Named in Atlanta</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   David Simpson, a newsman in the Atlanta bureau of
The Associated Press, has been named news editor there.
   The appointment was announced Monday by Chief of Bureau Carl
Bell.
   Simpson, 31, is a native of Greenville, Miss., and a graduate of
the University of Alabama. He worked for The Tuscaloosa (Ala.) News
and The Selma (Ala.) Times-Journal before joining the AP in Atlanta
in 1982.
   Simpson succeeds Charlotte Porter, who has been promoted to
assistant chief of bureau in Atlanta.
