<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--PrairieFire     04-03 0119</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Prairie Fire,0123</SECOND>
<HEAD>Prairie Fire Burns Wide Area in Inner Mongolia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A prairie fire burning out of control for five
days spread across 40 square miles of Inner Mongolia in northeast
China, the official Xinhua News Agency said Monday.
   The blaze destroyed 24,700 acres of grassland and jumped a fire
belt cleared by firefighters, the report said.
   Officials have called in 1,500 people, including forest guards,
soldiers and residents, to battle the blaze, Xinhua said.
Reinforcements were being called in.
   No casualties were reported.
   The fire occurred in a southern section of the Daxinganling
mountain region, which also suffered a devastating forest fire in
1986. That fire burned for a month and killed 193 people.
</TEXT>
