<FIRST>u i AM-Italy-TrainDerails     04-03 0219</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Italy-Train Derails,0224</SECOND>
<HEAD>Train Derails, Killing 5</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SEVERO, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A train that may have been speeding
derailed as it entered the station in this southern city Monday,
wrecking the bar and a ticket booth and killing at least five
people, officials reported.
   Two coaches slammed into the station wall, causing the bar to
collapse and demolishing the ticket booth and the freight and
baggage section, the reports said.
   A national police official in San Severo said five bodies had
been found and 16 injured people were hospitalized. The officer,
speaking on condition of anonymity, said the death toll could rise
because rescue workers still were searching the rubble.
   He said it was not clear whether the casualties had been on the
train or in the station, but the news agency AGI said the station
manager was among the dead.
   Smoke poured from holes in the coaches as workers helped pull
the wounded out. Other rescuers used dogs to search in the debris.
   Railroad authorities said it appeared the train was going faster
than the customary speed of about 18 mph when it entered the
station, Italian news agencies reported.
   The eight-car train arrived Monday afternoon in San Severo, 135
miles southeast of Rome, from the Tyrrhenian port of Bari, and had
been scheduled to return.
</TEXT>
