<FIRST>u f AM-Bonds     04-03 0498</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bonds,0521</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bond Prices Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bond prices strengthened Monday, although they
were knocked off their highs of the day by central bank action to
knock down the value of the dollar.
   The Treasury's key 30-year bond rose $3.13 per $1,000 in face
amount and its yield, which moves inversely, fell to 9.06 percent
from 9.09 percent late Friday.
   The central banks' dollar sales were more effective than usual
because the Bank of Japan joined in the dollar-lowering efforts
after a long absence from intervention.
   Finance ministers of seven major industrialized democracies said
Sunday after a meeting they would combat the dollar's appreciation
by selling the currency in coordinated intervention.
   Bonds held their gains for awhile after the dollar began its
descent but eventually weakened, said Marilyn Cohen, an analyst at
Capital Insight Inc. in Beverly Hills, Calif.
   An outlook for a declining dollar makes investors reluctant to
invest in dollar-denominated securities as well as raising the risk
of inflation spurred by more costly imported goods.
   The bond market was helped by a report the Nationalf Purchasing Management
released over the weekend that suggested
economic growth slowed significantly in March.
   The reporther eased fears of inflation and higher interest
rates, which hurt the value of fixed-income investments such as.
   Another report released Monday by the Cotment showed
construction spending remained unchanged in Februay, viewed as
another signal the economy is slowing.
   In thedary market for Treasury bonds, prices of short,-term governments
rose about \ to about ] point, the
financial information service Telerate Inc. reported. The movement
of a pnt is equals a change of $10 in the price of a bond with a
$1,0e value.
   The Shearson Lehman Hutton Daily Treasury Bond Index, which
measures price movements on all outstanding Treasury issues with
maturities of a year or longer, ros 1,124.77.
   In corporate trading, industrials also strengthened. Moody's
Investment Grade Corporate Bond Inures price
movements on 80 corporate bonds with maturities of fears or
longer, rose 0.92 to 299.07.
   In th the Bond Buyer index of 40 actively
traded municipal bonds rosint to 90\. The average yield to
maturity dropped to 7.78 percent from 7.79 percent late Friday.
   Yields on three-month Treasury bills fell to 9.12 percent as the
discount fell 5 basis points to 8.81 percent. Yields on six-month
bills fell to 9.38 percent as the di basis points to
8.86 percent. Yields on one-year bills fell to 9.45 percent as the
discount fell 10 basis poi to 8.74 percent.
   A basis point is one-hundredth of a percent. The yield
is the annualized return on an investment in a Trasury bill. The
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face
value, which is paid at maturity.
   The federal funds rate, the interest on overnight loans between
banks, traded at 9~ percent, down from 10 percent late Friday.
</TEXT>
